track_notes: A steep climb on a public right of way to the summit. Caution coming down can be very slippery...

This route leads from the railway station of the Isle of Man Steam Railway in Port Erin. The main bus stop is nearby. Caution on the cliffs of Bradda Head - it isnt too dangerous in my opinion. Milners Tower is worth investigating. You can usually climb to the top, it doesnt get locked. Sadly not in the activation zone!
track_title: Bradda Hill from railway station Port Erin
